SUMMARY:Pitch Please #9
LOCATION:AI House\, Seattle\, WA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\n***Registration opens mid-June***\n\nJoin us fo
 r an energizing afternoon of pitches\, networking\, and deep dives into so
 me of Seattle's most promising early-stage AI startups!\n\n📅 When: Once
  a month\, 2.5-hour afternoon sessions\n\n✨ What’s Happening?\n\nPitch
  Session (1.5 hours)\nFive talented founders take the stage selected from 
 the AI2 Incubator applicant pool (apply [here])\nEach founder gets 15 minu
 tes total:\n• 3 minutes to pitch\n• 6–7 minutes of candid feedback a
 nd Q&A from AI2 Incubator experts\, including:\nYifan Zhang Managing Dire
 ctor\, AI2 Incubator\n\nDan Koch\, Founder\, Lux Radium\; AI House Venture
  Partner\n\nFrank Chang\, Co-Founder and Managing Partner\, Flying Fish Pa
 rtners\n\nPlus\, 3 minutes of live audience Q&A for each founder—questio
 ns selected by our moderator.\nNetworking Mixer (1 hour): Stick around aft
 erward to network with founders\, potential co-founders\, investors\, and 
 AI enthusiasts.\n\n🚀 Audience Participation:\n\nAudience votes on their
  favorite pitch—"Audience Choice" winner automatically receives a guaran
 teed 1:1 meeting with AI2 Incubator.\n\n🔑 Post-Event Opportunities:\n\n
 AI2 selects which of the pitching founders (could be all 5) to invite for 
 follow-up 1:1 meetings\, exploring potential investment and incubation.\n\
 nWhether you're pitching\, exploring co-founder opportunities\, or simply 
 looking for inspiration\, join us and elevate your startup game!\n\nPlease
  note: These events are not open to investors or folks from banking.\nWe d
 o invite one guest VC to join the panel each time — if you’d like to b
 e considered\, feel free to email us directly!\n\nPlease note: RSVPing or 
 receiving an invite approval via Luma does not mean you’ve been selected
  to pitch. If you’re chosen\, someone from the AI2 Incubator team will r
 each out to you directly with next steps.\n\nCalendar: AI House Community 
 Events\n\nHosts: AI House\n\nVenue: AI House\n\nEvent page: https://luma.c
 om/11ppwn0t
URL:https://luma.com/11ppwn0t
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:evt-Px2ipUYVKDeDGwo@luma.com
DTSTAMP:20260706T023641Z
DTSTART:20260708T003000Z
DTEND:20260708T030000Z
SUMMARY:Moms Who Build: Maternal Health Hackathon — An AInChai + Armoire 
 Meetup
LOCATION:Armoire\, Seattle\, WA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nMoms Who Build — An AInChai Meetup\n\n☕ Cof
 fee + AI + Community\n\nWe're moms. We meet. We talk about our real lives 
 — the messy\, beautiful\, exhausting\, hilarious parts. And then we buil
 d something.\n\nThis July we're doing something a little different.\n\nMat
 ernal health and mom-focused organizations are bringing real\, unsolved pr
 oblems into the room — the gaps they see every day\, the things that don
 't exist yet\, the solutions they don't have the technical capacity to bui
 ld.\n\nAnd we're going to build them. Together. That night.\n\nNobody unde
 rstands what needs to be built for mom life better than the people living 
 it. So this time\, moms and builders are the ones in the driver's seat.\n\
 nHere's how the night works:\n\nOrganizations present real problems — 3 
 minutes each\, no fluff. Then we form teams — moms\, builders\, anyone w
 ho wants to help — and spend 60 minutes building a solution using AI too
 ls. A landing page\, a workflow\, a prototype\, an app. Something real\, n
 ot a slide deck.\n\nEvery team presents back to the organization at the en
 d.\n\nYou don't need to be technical. You don't need experience. You just 
 need to show up.\n\nThe night includes:\n\nA fireside conversation about b
 uilding something while raising someone — the honest version\, not the h
 ighlight reel.\n\nA build sprint — real problems from real organizations
 \, real teams\, real output in 60 minutes.\n\nOn-site babysitting provided
  by Rosie — because you shouldn't have to choose between showing up and 
 being a mom. Kids are welcome and cared for so you can fully be in the roo
 m.\n\nLight bites. Good company. The kind of room where you feel like your
 self again.\n\nWho this is for\n\nMoms who are building something — or w
 ant to. Builders who want to work on something that actually matters. Anyo
 ne who believes the people closest to a problem are the best ones to solve
  it.\n\nWhat to bring\n\nA laptop. Curiosity. Free Lovable credits will be
  provided for the build session. And if you have little ones — bring the
 m too. Rosie has babysitting covered on site.\n\nCome as you are. Leave ha
 ving built something real.\n\n🔁 Prompt. Plan. Build. Repeat.\n\n🌐 ww
 w.ainchai.com\n\nSponsored by:\n\nLovable — The AI-powered building plat
 form. The build credits provided for every attendee\n\nArmoire — designe
 r clothing rental\, proudly hosting Moms Who Build at their SODO boutique\
 n\nChildcare partner: Rosie — On-site babysitting so every mom can be fu
 lly present.\n\n​​About AInChai\n\nAInChai helps non-technical builder
 s learn AI\, ship products\, and grow — through training\, consulting\, 
 and tools made for real people. Learn more at www.ainchai.com\n\nBy regist
 ering for or attending this event\, you consent for the hosts and its affi
 liates to use your name\, image\, and likeness in any marketing related to
  the event. This consent includes\, without limitation\, an irrevocable\,
  perpetual\, worldwide\, fully-paid\, royalty-free\, sub-licensable\, non-
 transferable license to use any photographs or video recording on you take
 n while in attendance at the event. You also consent to receiving emails f
 rom the event hosts and sponsors.\n\nCalendar: AInChai\n\nHosts: Suha Tirm
 izi\, Annie Barker\, Rosie\n\nVenue: Armoire\n\nEvent page: https://luma.c
 om/20wq6b8g
URL:https://luma.com/20wq6b8g
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
