DTSTART:20260711T190000Z
DTEND:20260711T220000Z
SUMMARY:Seattle Code & Coffee @ Internet.Dev!
LOCATION:1928 Pike Pl suite 301\, Seattle\, WA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nCode and Coffee is an inclusive\, informal co-w
 orking session. People of all skill levels attend\, and we love it that wa
 y. Many people bring projects to work on\, and many other people socialize
  the entire time. It's entirely up to you!\n\n👋 The Introduction Circle
 \nAround 30 minutes into the event (12:30 pm)\, we will do a standup in a 
 circle.\nRound 1:\n\nYour name\n\nYour occupation/professional interests\n
 \nWhat would you like help with?\n\nRound 2:\n\nJob opportunities you're h
 iring for OR announce that you are looking for one. If not\, that's cool.\
 n\nCommunity events you wanna plug\n\nAfter the intro circle\, everything 
 is self-organized!\n\n🛠️ Tech Workshops\nWe offer the following works
 hops after the intro circle. These are free for all and hosted by friends/
 volunteers at C&C! If you have specialty knowledge you'd like to share\, o
 r wish to find an audience for your tech talk\, please reach out to any of
  our volunteers or @ us on discord!\n\nSecuring AI Coding Agents: Sandboxe
 s\, Trade-offs\, and Developer Experience - Yason Khaburzaniya\n\nAI codin
 g agents let you code 10 times faster than ever before\, but running them 
 safely is not a trivial task. We will go over dangers of running unsecured
  agents and the trade offs when securing them. Attendees will learn the st
 eps required to properly secure their coding agents inside sandboxes witho
 ut sacrificing developer experience.\n\n☕ Free coffee!\nPlease RSVP to s
 ecure your spot and help us get an accurate count on coffee.\n\n🅿️ Pa
 rking advisory\nUnfortunately\, no parking will be provided for this event
 . Plenty street parking options are availble near pike place market.\n\n
 ↪ Detailed location\n\nFind us on...\nDiscord\nLinkedIn\nWebsite\nWe wil
 l be looking to take photos during the meetup. 📸 Let one of the organiz
 ers know if you would rather we not include you in the photos!\n\nFind out
  more about Internet Development Studio's history\, mission\, and vision!\
 n\nCalendar: Seattle Code & Coffee\n\nHosts: Ryan Ren\, Sumitra Chhetri\n\
 nVenue: 1928 Pike Pl suite 301\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/jjfz3zut
URL:https://luma.com/jjfz3zut
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
