DTEND:20260717T023000Z
SUMMARY:Climate Change and Healthcare: Is the industry meant to heal us hur
 ting us?
LOCATION:Experience Momentum\, Seattle\, WA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nUPDATE: TIME\, DATE AND LOCATION CONFIRMED.\n\n
 What does the healthcare industry have to do with climate change? More tha
 n you might think. Join us for a 45 minute presentation with time for Q&A 
 that digs into one of the biggest paradoxes of the climate conversation: t
 he very industry intended to keep us healthy might also be contributing to
  the crisis that threatens our health in the first place. We'll look at ho
 w climate-related diseases and illnesses are reshaping the medical world\,
  and whether healthcare is rising to meet that challenge or quietly making
  things worse.\n\nSpeakers:\n\nMcKenna Parnes\, PhD\, MSEd is a clinical p
 sychologist and researcher in Seattle\, WA. Her work focuses on the inters
 ections between youth mental health and climate change\, with consideratio
 n of the ethical responsibility society holds in protecting and promoting 
 the health and well-being of younger and future generations.\n\nAdam Lough
 \, MHA is a Sr. Strategic Advisor at the Wilshire group with a background 
 spanning healthcare sustainability\, revenue cycle\, supply chain\, and he
 alth systems management. His work is driven by the conviction that a healt
 hier healthcare system\, for patients\, communities\, and the planet\, is 
 achievable.\n\nAgenda:\n\nDoors open at 6pm.\n\nPresentation begins at 6:1
 5pm.\n\n45 min presentation with Q&A.\n\nDrinks and snacks will be availab
 le.\n\nCalendar: Personal\n\nHosts: Adam L\, PNW Climate Week\, McKenna Pa
 rnes\n\nVenue: Experience Momentum\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/nvmb4x4
 b
URL:https://luma.com/nvmb4x4b
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
