 graph technology. We’re trading massive conference halls for a high-sign
 al environment where the person sitting next to you is just as likely to h
 ave the answer to your scaling bottleneck as the person on stage.\n\nWe’
 re already locking in sessions on the frontiers of the graph stack:\n\nGra
 phRAG & Graphs as Memory: Architectural patterns for the AI era.\n\nContex
 t Graphs & Hypervectors: Moving beyond simple nodes and edges.\n\nGetting 
 into Production: Real talk on crossing the chasm for enterprise implementa
 tions.\n\nClosing AMA Reverse Hackaton (plus networking) where the attende
 es bring the problems\, and our experts try to solve them live! Vaibhav Gu
 pta will be our 'Architect-in-Chief\,' moderating the chaos and keeping th
 e collaboration on track!\n\nSpecial thanks to our sponsors: \nSenzing\, N
 eo4j\, Google\, Arango\, Boundary\, gdotv\, and Generationship.\n\nMore De
 tails: https://www.graphgeeks.org/graphcon\n\n*This is a private event tha
 t requires pre-registration and approval. Ticket price of $45.00 includes 
 10.55% Washington State Sales Tax and 5% Seattle Admission Tax.\n\nCalenda
 r: GraphGeeks\n\nHosts: Amy Hodler\, Michelle Yi\n\nEvent page: https://lu
 ma.com/17qq1jmr
