DTEND:20260728T030000Z
SUMMARY:Creativity\, Intent\, and the Future of AI // A TEDxSeattle Salon a
 t Seattle Tech Week
LOCATION:Art Love Salon\, Seattle\, WA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nWhen machines can generate art\, text\, and mus
 ic in seconds\, what does it truly mean to be a creator?\n\nJoin us for a 
 brilliant\, multi-disciplinary panel discussion that moves past the usual 
 AI hype to explore the deeper intersection of human intention and artifici
 al intelligence. We are bringing together leading minds across music\, con
 temporary art\, neuroscience\, digital authenticity\, and ideas-led curati
 on to unpack how we preserve our creative voices in a rapidly shifting lan
 dscape.\n\nWe’ll dive deep into the questions that matter most to the fu
 ture of culture and innovation:\n\nThe Definition of Creation: How do we d
 efine creativity when machines can "create"?\n\nThe Root of Originality: I
 n a world of infinite synthesis\, what actually makes an idea original?\n\
 nGuarding the Voice: How do creators leverage AI as a tool without losing 
 their unique perspective?\n\nAmplication vs. Intention: How can AI help id
 eas travel further while humans remain the core source of truth and intent
 ?\n\nWhether you are an artist\, a builder\, a researcher\, or simply curi
 ous about the future of human ingenuity\, this conversation will change ho
 w you view the tools of tomorrow.\n\nThe Panelists\n\nMedearis Dixon – G
 rammy-Award Winning Musician\n\nBarry Johnson – Renowned Contemporary Ar
