SUMMARY:The Network Effect: Women Building Community in Tech and Leadership
  | Armoire x Boss Babes
LOCATION:Armoire\, Seattle\, WA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nThe path through tech and leadership is rarely 
 a solo climb — it's shaped by the people who open doors\, share hard-won
  advice\, and pull others up alongside them. But building that community c
 an feel like its own full-time job\, especially in fields where women are 
 outnumbered and the most important opportunities travel through networks y
 ou may not yet have access to.\n\nJoin us for a panel conversation with th
 e women building communities that solve exactly this. Our panelists are fo
 unders and leaders of organizations creating real connection\, mentorship\
 , and sponsorship for women in engineering\, technical roles\, and leaders
 hip — the kind of relationships that help you navigate big organizations
 \, find your next role\, and grow a career on your terms.\n\nExpect honest
  stories\, practical advice\, and authentic connection. Parking is free. L
 ight bites and coffee will be provided.\n\nCalendar: Armoire Events\n\nHos
 ts: Morgan Cundiff\, Kari Parker\n\nVenue: Armoire\n\nEvent page: https://
 luma.com/r0i73wed
URL:https://luma.com/r0i73wed
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
