SUMMARY:Women Founders & Funders Poker Night hosted by Project W & Armoire
LOCATION:Armoire\, Seattle\, WA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nAt most Seattle Tech Week events\, you work the
  room. Here\, you read it.\n\nYou'll sit across the felt from the founders
 \, investors\, and operators moving this ecosystem. Calling\, raising\, an
 d bluffing your way into the kind of conversations a quick hello never get
 s you to.\n\nNo real money\, but real stakes: who you walk out knowing.\n\
 nExpert dealers run every table\, so whether you've never held a hand or y
 ou play to win\, you can participate.\n\nSeats are limited - last year sol
 d out!\n\nAbout Project W\nProject W helps women achieve positions of infl
 uence—as CEOs\, business and professional leaders\, and investors—wher
 e they drive positive change and make a lasting impact. We do that through
  our programs for women entrepreneurs\, our peer communities\, and our sup
 port of women funders.\n\nAbout Armoire\nArmoire is the Seattle-based\, fe
 male-founded clothing rental membership that helps ambitious women love wh
 at they’re wearing. Armoire's curated recommendations and stylist picks 
 save you time and make it easy to refresh your wardrobe in a sustainable w
 ay. From work to weekends\, vacations to special events\, you can rent sty
 les for every occasion. Seattle members receive same-day deliveries or can
  visit our SODO member lounge to find the perfect styles to rent.\n\nCalen
 dar: Personal\n\nHosts: Project W\n\nVenue: Armoire\n\nEvent page: https:/
 /luma.com/pu52qo0e
URL:https://luma.com/pu52qo0e
