SUMMARY:STW Startup Showcase at The Showbox (Live Demos) | J.P. Morgan
LOCATION:Seattle\, WA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nDiscover the Future of Innovation at the Seattl
 e Tech Week Startup Showcase!\n\nSeattle definitely has something goin' on
 . We count ourselves continuously the underdog when it comes to the talent
  to investment ratio... but it's time to change that. Word is out that Sea
 ttle has 23% of the country's AI engineering talent\, and the startup ecos
 ystem is growing fast!\n\nCome check out what's going on up here. If you'r
 e an investor from out of state curious about Seattle\, this is an event y
 ou won't want to miss!\n\nOr perhaps you're a startup founder looking to c
 onnect with industry leaders and showcase your innovative ideas? Look no f
 urther! J.P. Morgan is thrilled to present the 2nd annual Seattle Tech Wee
 k Startup Showcase\, a marquee event at the Showbox Theater dedicated to h
 ighlighting the region's most innovative founders and their companies.\n\n
 Join us at the iconic Showbox Theater\, where the hottest startups in the 
 PNW will gather to demo\, pitch\, and network. We've partnered with local 
 VC funds and Seattle ecosystem partners to curate a showcase featuring the
  best of the best in the PNW.\n\nEvent Highlights\n\nOn stage:\n\nEarly St
 age Demos: This pitch competition will spotlight Angel to Pre-Seed startup
 s\n\nProduct Demos: Experience cutting-edge innovations from Seed to Serie
 s C companies.\n\n"Recently Raised": Cameos from the Founders of some of S
 eattle's Unicorn companies and biggest funding rounds in the last year  (n
 ew this year)\n\nInvestor Reverse Pitches from investors near and far!\n\n
 At the Showbox:\n\nInvestor & VIP Section - we will have part of the house
  reserved for VIPs and investors so you will be sure not to miss the best 
 demos in town!  (new this year)\n\nDrink Tickets available for first 300 r
 egistrants\n\nSchedule for the Startup Showcase (2:30–9:00pm)\nSubject t
 o change\n\n2:30–4:30pm Startup Fair (Separate registration here)\n4:30
 –5:30pm Break\n6:00–9:00pm Live Demos \n8:30pm+ Live Music – Good Le
 ttuce!\n\nAbout your hosts\n\nAbout J.P. Morgan\n\nJ.P. Morgan serves star
 tups and venture-backed high-growth companies\, founders and venture capit
 al firms across the globe in industries like technology\, fintech\, disru
 ptive commerce and internet\, life sciences\, climate tech and health tech
 . The firm provides deep industry expertise\, local support\, comprehensiv
 e solutions and services and a robust network of investors and partners to
  meet clients’ commercial\, investment and private banking needs. Learn 
 more at jpmorgan.com/innovationeconomy.\n\nBrought to you in partnership!
 \n\nThis event is greatly supported by the efforts of many Seattle area VC
 s and organizations: Ascend VC\, Madrona\, AI House\, Plug and Play Seattl
 e\, Anthos Capital\, and more!\n\nA big thank you to our additional financ
 ial sponsors: Google Cloud\, Pilot\, and Fenwick!\n\nAbout Google Cloud: G
 o from idea to impact faster with Google Cloud\, the AI hyperscaler for th
 e agentic era. We are in a category of one\, combining a complete\, first-
 party stack with an open ecosystem to build your competitive edge. Apply f
 or up to $350k in Google Cloud (and Gemini) credits.\n\nAbout Good Lettuce
 : Seattle’s premier 80s and 90s rock cover band\, featuring members from
  the VC\, big tech and startup communities. Grab a drink and sing along. Y
 ou’ll know 70% of the words to 90% of their songs.\n\nCalendar: JP Morga
 n Events\n\nHosts: JP Morgan\, Michelle Henry\n\nEvent page: https://luma.
 com/zbb6j727
URL:https://luma.com/zbb6j727
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
