SUMMARY:Orbital Data Centers\, Infrastructure and Connectivity with Ashurst
  Perkins Coie and Space Happy Hour
LOCATION:Seattle\, Washington
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nJoin Ashurst Perkins Coie and Space Happy Hour 
 for a Seattle Tech Week event.\n\nFrom launching the first AI chip in spac
 e to processing real-time data for civil\, defense\, and commercial custom
 ers\, unpack how space-based infrastructure is becoming the next critical 
 layer of AI and cloud computing. Grab a drink\, ask your boldest questions
 \, and connect with the community shaping the next frontier. Sign up befor
 e it fills up!\n\nSchedule\n👋📋5:00 p.m. – 5:30 p.m. PT: Check in \
 n🎤🙋5:30 p.m. – 6:15 p.m. PT: Panel discussion\n🌅🍻6:15 p.m. 
 – 8:00 p.m. PT: Sunset networking happy hour\n\nModerator\nBen Straughan
 \, Ashurst Perkins Coie\n\nPanelists\n\nDerek Huerta\, CEO\, Eclipse Space
 \nPhilip Johnston\, CEO\, Starcloud\nBrian Monnin\, CCO & Co-Founder\, Sop
 hia Space\n\nAshurst Perkins Coie's Emerging Companies & Venture Capital l
 awyers are trusted advisors to the world’s most innovative companies and
  most visionary investors. We support startup clients from formation to ex
 it with comprehensive legal and business counseling. Our clients have rais
 ed more than $15 billion in the private markets over the past three years 
 between the pre-seed and growth stage. Our extensive corporate law experie
 nce\, combined with sector-specific business and product counseling\, ensu
 re our services are tailored to each client's unique needs\, investor expe
 ctations\, and growth trajectories in cutting-edge industries like AI\, ae
 rospace and defense tech\, fintech\, digital health\, gaming\, energy inno
 vation\, digital media\, and consumer packaged goods.\n\nSpace Happy Hours
  are informal gatherings of companies in the space industry as well as tho
 se in the broader space ecosystem. We offer lively events at breweries as 
 well as exclusive events at space companies.\n\nCalendar: Personal\n\nHost
 s: Craig Baerwaldt\, Ashurst Perkins Coie\n\nEvent page: https://luma.com/
 0t8sk6py
