SUMMARY:System Override: Seattle Tech Week Rave - mpathic\, Fuel Talent\, S
 VB & Fenwick - 7:15 to 1 AM!!
LOCATION:Q Nightclub\, Seattle\, WA
DESCRIPTION:Source: Luma\n\nSeattle Tech Week’s most community building p
 arty is back — and this year we’re going full Y2K. This is the night w
 here Seattle’s tech community trades laptops for lasers and takes over t
 he dance floor.\n\nLast year you danced the night away and left with meani
 ngful connections that you couldn’t have made at a random tech happy hou
 r. This year\, we’re pushing the system to its limits: FULL SYSTEM OVERR
 IDE.\n\nStep into a glitchy\, high-energy rave with throwback Y2K vibes\, 
 immersive visuals\, and nonstop music from DJs across tech and the local s
 cene. Just like last year\, all of our DJs and artists are local AI and te
 ch builders\, engineers\, and\, oh yeah\, one VC.\n\n✨ Custom light show
  by local artists building with visual AI tools 🍸 Free drink tickets fo
 r the first two hours \n 💫 Rave swag\, surprises\, and good energy\n\n
 💿  DJ lineup: DJs Kirby\, Daniel Sahn\, Shep\, Siyan\, Quoth the Raver
  (Soundry AI)\, Cashmara (mpathic)\, Latinum and more! \n\nWe heard you: S
 ome improvements from last year include: lots of Air Conditioning and larg
 e fans! More drink tickets (with sponsors also handing out tickets through
 out the night)! Faster door lines.\n\nIf you love EDM\, techno\, and danci
 ng with the people building the future — this is your night.\n\nImportan
 t details\n\n21+ only\n\nEach guest must RSVP individually\n\nCapacity is 
 limited\n\nCome as you are! This means arrive straight from your other tec
 h events OR change into comfy Y2K rave wear ahead of the rave.\n\nWe follo
 w a PLURR code of conduct — Peace\, Love\, Unity\, Respect\, and Respons
 ibility ❤️\n\nHosted by\nSVB\, Fenwick\, Fuel Talent\, mpathic and Sou
 ndry AI\n\nRegistration\nFree entry + drink tickets with RSVP until 10pm\;
  after 10pm doors also open to the public. \n21+ only — each guest must 
 have their own ticket on Luma at entry.\n\nCalendar: Personal\n\nHosts: Re
